BT 1 0 0 1 0 99 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (The Lyapunov exponent lambda_L measures how fast nearby trajectories in a dynamical system diverge. lambda_L < 0:) Tj T* (stable attractor \(frozen\). lambda_L = 0: edge of chaos \(maximum information processing\). lambda_L > 0: chaotic) Tj T* -0.012882 Tw (divergence \(collapsed\). This maps exactly to the Wike phase diagram: frozen / edge / collapsed. Kauffman \(1993\) proposed) Tj T* 0 Tw (that evolution finds the edge of chaos \(lambda_L ~= 0\) because computation is maximized there. Goldberger \(2002\)) Tj T* (showed that healthy heart rate variability has Lyapunov structure consistent with lambda_L ~= 0, and that disease pushes) Tj T* (HRV toward lambda_L < 0 \(rigid, frozen, low entropy\) or lambda_L > 0 \(chaotic, noisy, high entropy\). This paper formally) Tj T* -0.101143 Tw (maps lambda_L to gamma_eff and shows that Goldberger's HRV-as-health-indicator IS the Wike Coherence Law measured) Tj T* 0 Tw (from the outside via the heart. The clinical implication: lambda_L calculated from HRV time series is a direct readout of) Tj T* (where a patient sits on the Wike phase diagram -- more informative than any single biomarker.) Tj T* ET
